==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retinophora
<hw>Ret`i*noph"o*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Retiniphorae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL.,
fr. NL. & E. <ets>retina</ets> + Gr. <grk>fe`rein</grk> to bear.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of group of two to four united cells which
occupy the axial part of the ocelli, or ommatidia, of the eyes of
invertebrates, and contain the terminal nerve fibrillae. See
<xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Ommatidium</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retinophoral</ent>⟦br⟧
